{
  "monologue": "Brief rationale: Your profile shows a preference for structure and small, verifiable steps. Adding a brief post-meal reflection along with a simple pre-eating intention preserves routine, reinforces logging, and supports progress without increasing cognitive load.",
  "utterance": "Fantastic commitment. Add a tiny post-meal check-in: after finishing your meal, spend 60 seconds to jot one line about what you ate and how full you felt. This keeps logging consistent and builds awareness. Before your next meal, keep your micro-steps but add a simple intention: 'I will notice the first fullness cue and stop there,' and log how that went. If cravings pop up, pause for two slow breaths and take a glass of water before continuing. This brief reflection with your existing plan helps steady progress toward your target behavior.",
  "endkey": false
}
